  "opposite_reasoning": "Incompetence provides the strongest practical opposite for CognitiveAuthorityAgents. It directly opposes the core semantic features: expertise, credibility, and capability. For AI safety monitoring, this axis is highly valuable - distinguishing competent authorities from incompetent actors helps detect false expertise claims, overconfidence, and misplaced trust. The concept has high availability (exists in both WordNet and SUMO), strong opposition strength (8/10), and excellent steering utility (9/10) for alignment applications. While 'Ignorance' scores slightly higher on availability, 'Incompetence' better captures the agent-level opposition (incompetent agents vs. authoritative agents) rather than just the knowledge-state opposition."
